title: For Sale/Trade:  Ruger Mark III,  not a plinker
postcontent: Please don't take the title the wrong way, but your average "Joe Plinker" will probably not want this gun.  I bought this one specifically for a certain type of competition and used it twice before losing interest and moving on to other things. The reason I say plinkers might not want this gun is that I had Volquartsen install their trigger upgrade.  This was not a cheap upgrade but I compete a lot and I understand what a huge effect a good trigger has on your scores.  If you are interested in enjoying this level of the Mark III Target grade .22, please familiarize yourself with Volquartsen.com and their products and pricing.  They are not cheap but what you get is an unbelievable trigger.  The standard trigger pull weight on these guns is about 5 to 6 pounds.  It is hard to shoot a tight group with that weight.  My groups and my scores, as well as my number of wins, went up dramatically after having this trigger installed.  I use a digital Lyman Trigger Pull Weight Gauge to check all my triggers.  This one consistently reads two pounds or LESS every time.  You really need to feel it to be able to appreciate the difference.  So, if you are already a good shooter who is ready to take your game to the next level with this incredible package, you owe it to yourself to check it out.  The gun is in immaculate condition, not a scratch or blemish anywhere.  Of course I include the original box and paperwork as well as all the factory parts that Volquartsen removed and replaced. You would be basically buying a very slightly used Mk III with the Volquartsen trigger upgrade for the same price as the gun sold for new.  As for trades, I am really not looking for anything in particular but I would be happy to hear about what you have if it is not just plain boring.  :-)    Feel free to respond to the ad directly or call or text with your questions, offers, etc during reasonable hours.  The ad automatically states that shipping is not an option.  That is not correct.  If you would like the gun shipped, I can work with you on that.  Thanks for looking! 864-363-49 fifty

postcontent:
Private Party Sale*Please read the listing before you contact me*Legal transfer only Will meet for transfer in North Metro Denver area onlyPurchase requires valid Colorado ID and background check approval*Smith and Wesson 422 .22LR Pistol..................................$ 370 -- Very good condition -- Adjustable sights -- 22 ounces  -- Aluminum frame -- 7.5" long over all -- 4.5" barrrel -- Includes One 10 round magazine -- No original box or paperwork*The following is from Wikipedia:*"Produced from 1987–1996, the Model 422 was the company's entry into the lucrative mid-priced rimfire pistol market. *A unique design feature of the 422, along with its variants, was the fact that the barrel, which was non-moving and was fixed to the frame.It resided in a low position in the frame just above the trigger guard. The barrel came threaded from the factory, with a protective "barrel nut" fitted. This made this pistol line perfect for use with a suppressor with an aftermarket adapter since the sights could still be utilized.
The bolt assembly, which comprised the top rearward portion of the pistol, moved behind as well as above the axis of the barrel and resembled an L shape. The recoil spring was contained in the portion above the bolt, which also housed the firing pin. Above the barrel was a large frame lug, which gave the gun a pleasing look of constant width and depth from the trigger guard forward to the muzzle.This also served as a solid block for the bolt to hit against when the recoil spring returned the bolt to battery. The low bore axis served to greatly reduce muzzle jump, and served to allow the fitting of a suppressor without losing the use of the factory sights.
The Model 422 was introduced with a 12-round detachable box magazine, but was later shipped with a 10-round magazine. The 1992 high-capacity magazine ban in California outlawed the sale of magazines with a capacity of more than 10 rounds."Call or TEXT REDACTED
